{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 19:25:06.445586", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content=\"You are provided with the following network description and its current state:\\nNetwork Description: This experiment uses a scalable SDN spine–leaf topology whose size depends on the selected topo_size.\\nEach leaf switch connects to all spine switches using point-to-point links.\\nEach leaf switch connects to two hosts belong to the same subnet 10.0.0.0/24.\\nAll switches also join a management network 20.0.0.0/24.\\nThe SDN controller resides at 20.0.0.100 and manages all switches via OpenFlow.\\nOVS switches: leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1\\nHosts: host_1_1, host_1_2, host_2_1, host_2_2\\nTopology: (leaf_1:eth0, host_1_1:eth0), (leaf_1:eth1, host_1_2:eth0), (leaf_2:eth0, host_2_1:eth0), (leaf_2:eth1, host_2_2:eth0), (spine_1:eth0, leaf_1:eth2), (spine_1:eth1, leaf_2:eth2), (spine_1:eth2, leaf_1:eth3)\\n\\nYour goal is to analyze the network condition and, if needed, use the available tools.\\nYou need to generate a troubeshooting diagnosis report.\\nThe report should reflect your assessment of the network's health, indicate any abnormal behavior you identify, and describe relevant findings based on your analysis.\\n\\nFocus on producing an informative and coherent diagnostic report derived from the network state.\\nDo not need to propose any solutions or remediation steps at this stage.\" additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='37eaf281-8776-41d7-8450-3492ac63585a'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
